author: Gerard Baker
title: The 10-Point.
text:
Good morning,
A Deal at Last
Washington’s budget stalemate appears to be over—for now. Congressional leaders have reached an agreement on a two-year deal, charting a departure from the tumult over spending and immigration that led to last month’s government shutdown and left long-term funding in jeopardy. The agreement raises spending by almost $300 billion over two years above limits imposed by a 2011 budget law and suspends the debt limit through March 1, 2019.
